	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Delay is also accounted for in the offhand, however what you need to consider is the RATIO of the dmg/dly for your offhand. While 9/18 is good for your mainhand, you would be better off with 12/26 or 11/25 in the offhand. <br><br>Mostly this is because of the damage bonus given to the mainhand (and not offhand). With the damage bonus you end up with a greater dmg with the same delay. However in the offhand, there is no bonus and you want to go with a good ratio, most usually a higher damage weapon.<br><br>So when you see those warriors using 2 lammy's or a monk using two wu sticks, you figure it's for looks or because they don't know. I would much rather use either a sarnak skullsplitter (or green jade broadsword) in the offhand, or for my monk at his level his fist is just fine.<br><br>Hope that helps some bro.<br><br>-Haruchai</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
